                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102H/326: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-02T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1919—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your June 9 and 21 regarding Harbin.</p>
                <p>Department giving matter careful consideration but desires consult Consul Moser,
                    expected in Washington soon, before reaching any definite decision.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
